description._content: Catalog #: 09_01766 Title: Frederick A. Hoover Special Collection Photo Additional Information: Frederick A. Hoover in a Wright Brothers built aircraft. Handwritten Inscription ""My first flight made at Baldwin park, Quincy ILL. June 8th 1912"", Frederick A. Hoover was the 100th individual to receive his aviator license (June 8th 1912). He performed stunts in air shows and was known as 'The Death Cheating Aviator"". He was a member of the Early Birds of Aviation. Corporation Name: Wright Tags: Frederick A.
